The article announces the continuation of the national emergency with respect to significant narcotics traffickers centered in Colombia. This emergency was initially declared in 1995 and is being extended for another year due to the ongoing threat posed by these traffickers. The actions of these traffickers continue to harm the national security, foreign policy, and economy of the United States, as well as cause violence and corruption both domestically and internationally. The notice states that this continuation is in accordance with the National Emergencies Act and will be published in the Federal Register and transmitted to Congress. The announcement is made by President Barack Obama.